            "text": "1Chronicles 28:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "As king instead of David his father.—It is not meant that David abdicated. 1Chronicles 29:23-25 are anticipative of the history of Solomon’s reign. At the same time, their introduction here is natural, not only as relating the immediate sequel of Solomon’s coronation, but also as showing how David’s last wishes in regard to his son were realised.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "As king instead of David his",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "father.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—It is not meant that David abdicated. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 29:23-25",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " are anticipative of the history of Solomon’s reign. At the same time, their introduction here is natural, not only as relating the immediate sequel of Solomon’s coronation, but also as showing how David’s last wishes in regard to his son were realised.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
