  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "29:20-25 This great assembly joined with David in adoring God. Whoever is the mouth of the congregation, those only have the benefit who join him, not by bowing down the head, so much as by lifting up the soul. Solomon sat on the throne of the Lord. Solomon's kingdom typified the kingdom of the Messiah, whose throne is the throne of the Lord.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The throne of David is called here \"the throne of the Lord,\" as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 28:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " it is called \"the throne of the kingdom of the Lord,\" because God had set it up and had promised to establish it. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "23. Solomon sat on the throne of the Lord—As king of Israel, he was the Lord's vicegerent.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "On the throne of the Lord, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " i.e. on the throne of Israel, which is called the throne of the Lord, either more generally, as all thrones are the Lord’s, by whom kings reign, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Proverbs 8:15",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 8:15",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and magistrates are ordained, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Romans 13:1,2",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Romans 13:1",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ",2",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; or more specially and peculiarly; either, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "1. Because the Lord himself was in a peculiar manner the King and Governor of Israel, not only in the time of the judges, but afterward, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Psalm 44:4 89:18 149:2 Isaiah 33:22",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Psalm 44:4",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " 89:18 149:2 ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Isaiah 33:22",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Or, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "2. Because it was the throne of Christ the Lord, whose vicegerents David, and Solomon, and their successors were, for whom this throne was reserved, and by whom it was to be established and enjoyed for ever, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Luke 2:32,33",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Luke 2:32",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ",33",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Or, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "3. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The throne of the Lord",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is put for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the throne of the people of the Lord",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", by a concise and short manner of speech, which is frequent in the Hebrew language; as when the key of David is put for the key of the house of David; and the mountain of the Lord, for the mountain of the Lord’s house. Or, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "4. Because this throne fell to Solomon not by right of inheritance, for he had elder brethren, but by the special appointment and gift of the Lord. And so this ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "of the Lord",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is the genitive case of the efficient, as the learned call it, and signifies ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "which the Lord gave him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
